concluded that it solves all black problems. The confirmation came soon from
one of the top players in the world.} 14. b5 (14. Bd2 {is more circumspect,
but also a bit too passive. Black obtains a good game after:} axb4 15. axb4
Rxa1 16. Rxa1 b5 17. e4 c5 $1 $132 {a strong pawn break in the spirit of the
Breyer variation of Ruy Lopez!} 18. dxc5 dxe4 19. Be2 Nxc5 $1 20. bxc5 Qxd2 $15
) 14... c5 15. Nxd5 a4 $1 {This is the key intermezzo that fixes pawn
structure on the queenside favourably and creates a possible outpost for the
knight on b3.} 16. Qa2 Nxd5 17. Bxd5 Bxd5 18. Qxd5 cxd4 19. exd4 ({In case of} 
19. Qxd4 Nc5 $44 {the knight travels to the fantastic b3-square.}) 19... Nf6
20. Qf3 Qxd4 21. Bg5 Qd5 22. Bxf6 Qxf3 23. gxf3 gxf6 $15 {1/2-1/2 (53)
Shankland,S (2671)-Ding,L (2778) Liaocheng 2018} *

