3. Nc3 Bb4 4. Qc2 b6 {[#] In this chapter, we will look at less critical
responses to 4...b6 system. The game usually transposes to various branches of
the 4...0-0 variation with ...b6. This leads to interesting middlegames that
have a much less forced character than the main lines of the 4.Qc2
Nimzo-indian. If White does not want to play principled and sharp 5.e4
variation, he usually goes for a more positional continuation:} 5. a3 {winning
the bishop pair at once.} ({White can also ignore the bishop on b4 and
activate his own bishop:} 5. Bg5 Bb7 {[#] Now, he has several developing
