$5 {is a good alternative, taking under control the squares on the h2-b8
diagonal. Black should develop as quickly as possible:} Nc6 ({Another option
is:} 11... Qb6 12. Kf2 Nc6 13. Rhd1 Ba5 14. Rab1 Nb4 15. Qh5 (15. Qd6 $5) 15...
Bd3 $1 16. Rbc1 {1-0 (24) Tabatabaei,M (2548)-Pashikian,A (2592) Yerevan 2017
and now:} c4+ 17. Be3 Qa6 $132 {would have given Black excellent counterplay
in the view of ...Nc2, ...Bb6 and ...f5!}) 12. Kf2 {This is a standard way to
evacuate the king in the 4.f3 variation. However, Black has a way to harrass
it even on f2:} c4 $1 $132 {[#] This not only opens up the g1-a7 diagonal, but
also establishes a potential outpost for ...Nc6-b4(e5)-d3 maneuver.} ({Too
static is} 12... Nd4 13. Rhd1 Qb6 14. Qd6 $14 {1-0 (48) Berkes,F (2661)-Szabo,
G (2563) Heraklio 2017}) 13. Rhd1 Be7 $1 {An excellent move. Black clears the
