exd5 14. cxd5 Bxd3 15. Qxd3 {and here Karpov obtained a positional advantage
with:} c4 $1 16. Qf3 Nb3 17. Rb1 Re8 18. O-O Ndc5 $15 {0-1 (52) Zakharov,A 
(2435)-Karpov,A (2695) Moscow 1976}) 9... h6 10. Bh4 {This pin is somewhat
unpleasant for Black, especially if he would like to castle kingside. Thus, it
