Bc5 16. a4 Re8 17. Nb3 Bd6 18. Be3 Bg6 19. Bd4 Ne4 $13 {1/2-1/2 Topalov,V 
(2780) -Gelfand,B (2737)/Nice 2008/CBM 123 Extra (35)}) (7. Nf3 {transposes to
the line 6.Nf3 dxc4 7.a3 Be7}) 7... exd5 8. Nh3 $5 c6 9. O-O {[#] White's
interesting development scheme has a point. He would like to get his knight to
f4, but he does it without having played e2-e3, as is usual in such positions.
The idea behind it is to leave e3-square available for white bishop, so that
